---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import bioPhoto from '../../public/images/crossed-legged.jpg'
---

<section id="bio" class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-cream-50">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <h2 class="text-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-center mb-16 scroll-reveal" data-delay="0">
      About
    </h2>

    <!-- Two-Column Layout -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center">
      <!-- Photo Column -->
      <div class="scroll-reveal" data-delay="1">
        <Image
          src={bioPhoto}
          alt="Ross Taylor Williams seated cross-legged in natural setting"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-md"
          loading="lazy"
          quality={85}
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Bio Text Column -->
      <div class="space-y-4 scroll-reveal" data-delay="2">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          Ross is a guitarist, producer, and composer based in Lawrence, KS. He draws from places that don't usually share a stage: the alternate tunings of Sonic Youth, the melody of Nick Drake and Andy Mckee, and the mystical power of Jack Rose and Led Zeppelin. 
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          <em>Earth Music</em> was born from a revelation: abandon all cleverness, analysis, and adherence to form. Follow only the emotional undercurrent of the sound, and surrender to whatever process it takes to realize work. No one need hear or even know about it. Transformation through devotion, for its own sake.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          The songs on <em>Earth Music</em> took years to write. Each went through months of iteration, moving between sheet music and the fretboard, passing through radically different versions before arriving at their final form. In recording, the process inverted: years of composing compressed into single takes, no overdubs. Nothing between the guitar and the listener.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
